00:12:05.800 --> 00:12:13.800
last remained central in our life as a church, as we worship together at Trinity Fellowship.

250
00:12:13.800 --> 00:12:18.800
Final thing there, another thing is that the word that is given to us isn't just true.

251
00:12:18.800 --> 00:12:20.800
It is precious.

252
00:12:20.800 --> 00:12:24.800
Right, so Paul, this word was given to Paul and the other apostles and prophets,

253
00:12:24.800 --> 00:12:28.800
we now receive it through the word we're being built up by it.

254
00:12:28.800 --> 00:12:33.800
And as we see it, we see that it's not just true, it is precious.

255
00:12:33.800 --> 00:12:38.800
So opening up the word isn't like just opening up an encyclopedia, it's opening up a treasure chest.

256
00:12:38.800 --> 00:12:40.800
You see that at the end of verse 8?

257
00:12:40.800 --> 00:12:45.800
It's here that we see all the treasures that are ours in Jesus.

258
00:12:45.800 --> 00:12:48.800
Right, so we had our opening scripture, Psalm 19.

259
00:12:48.800 --> 00:12:51.800
There we see God's glory as being revealed in creation.

260
00:12:51.800 --> 00:12:56.800
You think about the most beautiful, wonderful thing that you can imagine in the whole universe.

261
00:12:56.800 --> 00:13:02.800
Well, that is pointing to something that is even greater and that is the glory of God.

262
00:13:02.800 --> 00:13:06.800
And then the Psalm goes on to talk about God's glory being revealed in His Word.

263
00:13:06.800 --> 00:13:09.800
It is more to be desired than gold.

264
00:13:09.800 --> 00:13:12.800
It is sweeter than honey, right?

265
00:13:12.800 --> 00:13:17.800
So God is revealing His glory in His Word.

266
00:13:17.800 --> 00:13:22.800
And so now we have the word pointing to who Jesus is to us

267
00:13:22.800 --> 00:13:27.800
and what He has done in bringing us together into His people.

268
00:13:27.800 --> 00:13:31.800
So if it was the case before the God's Word was precious,

269
00:13:31.800 --> 00:13:35.800
how much more is it now that we have come to know Jesus,

270
00:13:35.800 --> 00:13:38.800
the one that the Word has been pointing to all along?

271
00:13:38.800 --> 00:13:40.800
Alright, so that's the mystery of the gospel.

272
00:13:40.800 --> 00:13:45.800
We can be part of the body of Christ together and receive all the blessings that come with that.

273
00:13:45.800 --> 00:13:50.800
Secondly, let's also see that Paul talks about the ministry of the gospel.

274
00:13:50.800 --> 00:13:53.800
So look at with me at verse 7.

275
00:13:53.800 --> 00:13:56.800
He says, of this gospel, of this good news,

276
00:13:56.800 --> 00:14:01.800
I was made a minister according to the gift of God's grace.

277
00:14:01.800 --> 00:14:02.800
Let's pause there.

278
00:14:02.800 --> 00:14:05.800
So Paul was made a minister.

279
00:14:05.800 --> 00:14:10.800
So many of you know I had the privilege of serving in England for a number of years

280
00:14:10.800 --> 00:14:15.800
and over in the UK pastors are often referred to as ministers.

281
00:14:15.800 --> 00:14:19.800
And so one of my boys was at school one day.

282
00:14:19.800 --> 00:14:20.800
It was a Gideon I believe.

283
00:14:20.800 --> 00:14:22.800
And his teacher sat him down.

284
00:14:22.800 --> 00:14:23.800
He was really little.

285
00:14:23.800 --> 00:14:25.800
And I think he was four or five years old.

286
00:14:25.800 --> 00:14:28.800
And they said, so your daddy's a minister.

287
00:14:28.800 --> 00:14:31.800
And he said, no, a prime minister.

288
00:14:31.800 --> 00:14:38.800
So I don't know if he thought, you know, I was kind of running the country in my spare time while he was at school.

289
00:14:38.800 --> 00:14:41.800
I don't know, it gave me a big head for a day or two.

290
00:14:41.800 --> 00:14:46.800
But when Paul refers to himself as a minister here, he's not kind of talking himself up.

291
00:14:46.800 --> 00:14:48.800
It's not that he's got a big head.

292
00:14:48.800 --> 00:14:51.800
He isn't kind of lauding his importance.

293
00:14:51.800 --> 00:14:53.800
It's an expression of humility.

294
00:14:53.800 --> 00:14:55.800
Right. The word literally means servant.

295
00:14:55.800 --> 00:14:58.800
He's saying, I'm a servant of the gospel.

296
00:14:58.800 --> 00:15:06.800
In fact, he puts himself even lower in verse eight when he refers to himself as the very least of all the saints.

297
00:15:06.800 --> 00:15:10.800
In fact, when you look at the original language here, you almost kind of like makes up a word, right?

298
00:15:10.800 --> 00:15:14.800
There's the word least and he adds another like thing to the end of it.

299
00:15:14.800 --> 00:15:16.800
So like, I'm not just the least. I'm the leaster.

300
00:15:16.800 --> 00:15:22.800
I'm not the least important or the lowest. I'm the lowest or lowest s s.

301
00:15:22.800 --> 00:15:25.800
He's like, however low you can imagine that, that's me.

302
00:15:25.800 --> 00:15:26.800
Why is he saying that?

303
00:15:26.800 --> 00:15:29.800
Well, it's not a kind of false humility here.

304
00:15:29.800 --> 00:15:34.800
It's the fact that he is deeply aware of what God has saved him from.

305
00:15:34.800 --> 00:15:41.800
If you go back and read the book of Acts, you see that he was once a persecutor of the church that he is now serving.

306
00:15:41.800 --> 00:15:47.800
And so God's grace has brought him that far from death to life, from darkness to light.

307
00:15:47.800 --> 00:15:51.800
You might wonder, then, well, how did this persecutor become a preacher?

308
00:15:51.800 --> 00:15:58.800
How is he the one through which God is giving this gospel out, making this mystery known?

309
00:15:58.800 --> 00:16:02.800
And what does this ministry tell us about ourselves?

310
00:16:02.800 --> 00:16:06.800
A couple of things. One is ministry is the work of God.

311
00:16:06.800 --> 00:16:09.800
We see that in Paul. That's how he became a minister.

312
00:16:09.800 --> 00:16:15.800
Not only God could have made Saul of Tarsus a minister of the gospel, this Paul that we read about here.

313
00:16:15.800 --> 00:16:17.800
And that's exactly how he describes it.

314
00:16:17.800 --> 00:16:21.800
First of all, notice Paul says, I was made a minister.

315
00:16:21.800 --> 00:16:23.800
That's passive language being used there.

316
00:16:23.800 --> 00:16:27.800
This isn't something that he did. It was something that was done to him.

317
00:16:27.800 --> 00:16:32.800
It was something that he had received from outside of himself.

318
00:16:32.800 --> 00:16:34.800
God did it. So how did God do it?

319
00:16:34.800 --> 00:16:37.800
We can talk about God's grace.

320
00:16:37.800 --> 00:16:41.800
Verse 7, he was made a minister according to God's grace.

321
00:16:41.800 --> 00:16:45.800
So apostleship wasn't kind of at the top of the vocational ladder he was climbing.

322
00:16:45.800 --> 00:16:51.800
It wasn't a position that he had earned or had worked for, anything like that.

323
00:16:51.800 --> 00:16:55.800
It was a gift freely given by God.

324
00:16:55.800 --> 00:17:03.800
God was pleased to pour out his grace upon him and give him this responsibility to make that grace known to others.

325
00:17:03.800 --> 00:17:07.800
So he's giving out of the grace that he has received from God.

326
00:17:07.800 --> 00:17:10.800
He doesn't just speak about God's grace making him a minister.

327
00:17:10.800 --> 00:17:14.800
He speaks about God's power making him a minister as well.

328
00:17:14.800 --> 00:17:19.800
The grace was given to him, he says, by the working of God's power.

329
00:17:19.800 --> 00:17:26.800
You may remember earlier in Ephesians, God's power was spoken of in relation to Jesus' resurrection.

330
00:17:26.800 --> 00:17:29.800
He was raised by God's power.

331
00:17:29.800 --> 00:17:33.800
And that same power was spoken of in terms of our own conversion.

332
00:17:33.800 --> 00:17:37.800
So when we come to faith in Christ, it's because we too are raised by God's power.

333
00:17:37.800 --> 00:17:41.800
God gives us new life in Christ, this power.

334
00:17:41.800 --> 00:17:48.800
So it was God's power that overcame the resistance of Saul when he became a minister of the gospel.

335
00:17:48.800 --> 00:17:55.800
It was God's power that brought him to himself and made him new in Christ.

336
00:17:55.800 --> 00:18:01.800
And it was God's power that was enabling him to carry out his calling now as a minister.

337
00:18:01.800 --> 00:18:05.800
And he also speaks not only of God's grace and power, but also God's purpose.

338
00:18:05.800 --> 00:18:07.800
So look at me at verse 2.

339
00:18:07.800 --> 00:18:13.800
At the beginning he talks about his ministry as being a stewardship of God's grace.

340
00:18:13.800 --> 00:18:19.800
That's the same word used in Ephesians chapter 1 and verse 10 to refer to God's plan, God's stewardship,

341
00:18:19.800 --> 00:18:22.800
to unite all things in Jesus.

342
00:18:22.800 --> 00:18:26.800
Now he's talking about Paul's talking about his role to carry out God's plans.

343
00:18:26.800 --> 00:18:28.800
So the idea is like God's made the plans.

344
00:18:28.800 --> 00:18:36.800
He's drawn up the blueprint and now Paul is getting to work fulfilling those plans according to God's will.

345
00:18:36.800 --> 00:18:44.800
So God's plan is to glorify himself by creating this global family called the church.

346
00:18:44.800 --> 00:18:49.800
And Paul's role here is to preach the gospel so that it is brought about.

347
00:18:49.800 --> 00:18:55.800
So it's according to the work of God, this work that God is doing through the gospel.

348
00:18:55.800 --> 00:18:57.800
That's how Paul was made a minister.

349
00:18:57.800 --> 00:19:01.800
But also I want us to see that it was for the good of others, for the good of others.

350
00:19:01.800 --> 00:19:09.800
Back when I was in Bible college years ago, I remember the pastor of the church that had kind of started this college

351
00:19:09.800 --> 00:19:14.800
preached from Ephesians chapter 3 and verse 2 to us students.

352
00:19:14.800 --> 00:19:20.800
And instead of preaching as normal that day, he just took the last four words of verse 2 as his sermon.

353
00:19:20.800 --> 00:19:22.800
It was to me, for you.

354
00:19:22.800 --> 00:19:25.800
And he kind of took the chance to give his testimony.

355
00:19:25.800 --> 00:19:29.800
And right the way he would start off and talk about how God had saved him.

356
00:19:29.800 --> 00:19:31.800
But that was given to me for you.

357
00:19:31.800 --> 00:19:34.800
And he started talking about the different ways God had worked in his life.

358
00:19:34.800 --> 00:19:35.800
Now he's an older man.

359
00:19:35.800 --> 00:19:39.800
He could just see that yes the Lord had been gracious to him but it wasn't just for himself.

360
00:19:39.800 --> 00:19:42.800
It was for others.

361
00:19:42.800 --> 00:19:44.800
He was learning that lesson.

362
00:19:44.800 --> 00:19:46.800
He wanted to drive that home to us and really stuck out.

363
00:19:46.800 --> 00:19:51.800
So Paul says what God had given was to him, yes, but it wasn't merely for him.

364
00:19:51.800 --> 00:19:53.800
It was for others.

365
00:19:53.800 --> 00:19:58.800
So Paul doesn't show us his LinkedIn profile here or some kind of resume.

366
00:19:58.800 --> 00:20:00.800
Like look at all my accolades.

367
00:20:00.800 --> 00:20:02.800
His ministry isn't for himself.

368
00:20:02.800 --> 00:20:04.800
It isn't self promotion.

369
00:20:04.800 --> 00:20:09.800
It's for the good that God was going to bring about in the lives of others through him.

370
00:20:09.800 --> 00:20:11.800
And it was so good seeing that happen.

371
00:20:11.800 --> 00:20:15.800
And he was even willing to, like if it meant Paul suffering, what God is doing through him,

372
00:20:15.800 --> 00:20:19.800
it's so glorious he's even willing to suffer to see that happen.

373
00:20:19.800 --> 00:20:22.800
So this is written from prison, you see in verse one.

374
00:20:22.800 --> 00:20:25.800
Paul is in prison for preaching the gospel.

375
00:20:25.800 --> 00:20:32.800
At the end of our section here in verse 13, Paul tells them he doesn't want them to be discouraged by his suffering.

376
00:20:32.800 --> 00:20:39.800
Because he's confident that God is accomplishing his good purposes through them in their lives.

377
00:20:39.800 --> 00:20:41.800
So what does that have to do with us then?

378
00:20:41.800 --> 00:20:44.800
This ministry of the gospel.

379
00:20:44.800 --> 00:20:50.800
Well one is what Paul went through in his preaching of the gospel has led to our good this morning.

380
00:20:50.800 --> 00:20:53.800
We are recipients of what Paul writes even here.

381
00:20:53.800 --> 00:20:55.800
We're recipients of this message.

382
00:20:55.800 --> 00:20:58.800
And so first, you know, we're called to respond to that gospel.

383
00:20:58.800 --> 00:21:00.800
But I want us to see what we can learn from his example.

384
00:21:00.800 --> 00:21:02.800
So here's how this applies to us.

385
00:21:02.800 --> 00:21:05.800
One is, you know, let's say we're recipients of that message.

386
00:21:05.800 --> 00:21:15.800
So the gospel that saved Paul, the grace that changed Paul's life, the power that raised him from the dead and gave him new life in Jesus can change anyone's life.

387
00:21:15.800 --> 00:21:17.800
It can change your life.

388
00:21:17.800 --> 00:21:22.800
The Lord can save you and he can use you for his glory.

389
00:21:22.800 --> 00:21:27.800
Another thing I want us to see is that we are all called to gospel ministry.

390
00:21:27.800 --> 00:21:30.800
If you read chapter four you'll see this.

391
00:21:30.800 --> 00:21:40.800
In chapter four verse seven we see that the same grace that had been given to Paul, gifting him, had been given to every single follower of Jesus.

392
00:21:40.800 --> 00:21:46.800
And Paul's role, the role of other church leaders like him was to equip God's people for the work of the ministry.

393
00:21:46.800 --> 00:21:49.800
Right? Because they are called to gospel ministry as well.

394
00:21:49.800 --> 00:21:50.800
And it lays that out.

395
00:21:50.800 --> 00:21:58.800
It shows how we're all called to serve one another in love that we might grow together in the likeness of Jesus.

396
00:21:58.800 --> 00:22:00.800
So we're all in gospel ministry.

397
00:22:00.800 --> 00:22:03.800
And gospel ministry is a gift.

398
00:22:03.800 --> 00:22:10.800
When we think about ministry and what we're doing here in the church, like this is not about self-actualization.

399
00:22:10.800 --> 00:22:16.800
It's about serving others out of the grace of God that has been given to us.

400
00:22:16.800 --> 00:22:22.800
It's about making Christ known for God's glory and for the good of those around me.

401
00:22:22.800 --> 00:22:29.800
Another thing is that kind of gospel ministry is difficult work, but it is worth it.

402
00:22:29.800 --> 00:22:30.800
It is so worth it.

403
00:22:30.800 --> 00:22:31.800
It involves suffering.

404
00:22:31.800 --> 00:22:35.800
Yes, you may even have to sit out in the cold.

405
00:22:35.800 --> 00:22:38.800
But it is worth it.

406
00:22:38.800 --> 00:22:43.800
It does all of us good to step back though and remember what an amazing privilege we have been given.

407
00:22:43.800 --> 00:22:54.800
That God would call people like us to himself and would use us for his good purposes in the lives of others and in the world at large.

408
00:22:54.800 --> 00:23:02.800
So I could just say that as we step into this week of thanksgiving, let's just pause and remember how much we have to be grateful to God for.

409
00:23:02.800 --> 00:23:05.800
God has been so gracious to us.

410
00:23:05.800 --> 00:23:06.800
He's given us his son.

411
00:23:06.800 --> 00:23:07.800
He's made us his own.

412
00:23:07.800 --> 00:23:10.800
And he's given us one another in the church.

413
00:23:10.800 --> 00:23:14.800
He's given us all of these promises we sang about and we've read about here.

414
00:23:14.800 --> 00:23:20.800
By the way, could I just say I'm so grateful for every one of you as well.

415
00:23:20.800 --> 00:23:26.800
The way you've been serving the Lord and serving one another here as this new church is getting started.

416
00:23:26.800 --> 00:23:32.800
It's been so evident that this work of the ministry is something that we are all involved in.

417
00:23:32.800 --> 00:23:36.800
I can't wait to see what the Lord accomplishes in the days ahead.

418
00:23:36.800 --> 00:23:40.800
However cold it gets to return to that thing.

419
00:23:40.800 --> 00:23:42.800
Let's remember to warm our hearts by this fire.

420
00:23:42.800 --> 00:23:43.800
God is gracious.

421
00:23:43.800 --> 00:23:44.800
God is powerful.

422
00:23:44.800 --> 00:23:46.800
God is accomplishing his purposes.

423
00:23:46.800 --> 00:23:50.800
This is about his glory and the good of others.

424
00:23:50.800 --> 00:23:52.800
So what is God doing here?

425
00:23:52.800 --> 00:23:55.800
Let's come to this final M.

426
00:23:55.800 --> 00:23:57.800
It's about the manifold wisdom of God.

427
00:23:57.800 --> 00:23:59.800
We read this in chapter three in verse 10.

428
00:23:59.800 --> 00:24:05.800
So Paul is carrying out this ministry, proclaiming the mystery rather.

429
00:24:05.800 --> 00:24:13.800
So that through the church, the manifold wisdom of God might now be made known.

430
00:24:13.800 --> 00:24:18.800
That's why we're here to display the manifold wisdom of God.

431
00:24:18.800 --> 00:24:20.800
That's why the church exists.

432
00:24:20.800 --> 00:24:23.800
If you know Christ, this is what you are part of.

433
00:24:23.800 --> 00:24:24.800
So what does that mean?

434
00:24:24.800 --> 00:24:26.800
This might be a surprising way if I were to ask you this morning,

435
00:24:26.800 --> 00:24:30.800
what's the purpose of the church to display the manifold wisdom of God?

436
00:24:30.800 --> 00:24:32.800
Would that be the first thing you could say?

437
00:24:32.800 --> 00:24:33.800
Not necessarily.

438
00:24:33.800 --> 00:24:35.800
So what does this mean here?

439
00:24:35.800 --> 00:24:38.800
Well manifold isn't even a word that we use every day here.

440
00:24:38.800 --> 00:24:42.800
So it essentially means multicolored.

441
00:24:42.800 --> 00:24:46.800
There was a Greek translation of the Old Testament that was being used at the time

442
00:24:46.800 --> 00:24:54.800
and that was the same exact word that was used to talk about Joseph's coat of many colors in Genesis 37.

443
00:24:54.800 --> 00:24:55.800
Right?

444
00:24:55.800 --> 00:25:01.800
So you've got this one coat, but you've got all of these different colors built into this one coat.

445
00:25:01.800 --> 00:25:02.800
This is God's wisdom.

446
00:25:02.800 --> 00:25:04.800
God's wisdom is not monochrome.

447
00:25:04.800 --> 00:25:07.800
It's multicolored and multivariate.

448
00:25:07.800 --> 00:25:14.800
So there's nothing unique about similar people getting together to do things that they all happen to enjoy.

449
00:25:14.800 --> 00:25:17.800
Like pickleball can bring people together.

450
00:25:17.800 --> 00:25:22.800
We can think of any number of common things that bring like-minded people together.

451
00:25:22.800 --> 00:25:24.800
But what God does in the church is unique.

452
00:25:24.800 --> 00:25:27.800
He takes different people from all different backgrounds

453
00:25:27.800 --> 00:25:32.800
and brings them together into one family, into this one body.

454
00:25:32.800 --> 00:25:39.800
And he does so in a way that has both variety present and unity together at the same time

455
00:25:39.800 --> 00:25:41.800
in this kind of coat of many colors.

456
00:25:41.800 --> 00:25:43.800
His wisdom is manifold.

457
00:25:43.800 --> 00:25:49.800
It's multicolored as he brings the churches together from people from all nations.

458
00:25:49.800 --> 00:25:52.800
Well who is this manifold wisdom being displayed to?

459
00:25:52.800 --> 00:25:56.800
So if God's manifold wisdom and glory is being displayed, who's looking on?

460
00:25:57.800 --> 00:25:59.800
What says at the end of verse 10?

461
00:25:59.800 --> 00:26:04.800
It's being displayed to the rulers and authorities in the heavenly places.

462
00:26:04.800 --> 00:26:10.800
So if God's redemption plan is like a drama, you can think of maybe him as like the writer and director.

463
00:26:10.800 --> 00:26:15.800
Maybe Christ as the lead role, but we also have a part to play in this as well.

464
00:26:15.800 --> 00:26:17.800
So who was the audience?

465
00:26:17.800 --> 00:26:19.800
It's the angels.

466
00:26:19.800 --> 00:26:20.800
The angels.

467
00:26:20.800 --> 00:26:23.800
It's interesting we don't often think of it in that way.

468
00:26:23.800 --> 00:26:24.800
At least I don't.

469
00:26:24.800 --> 00:26:26.800
John Stott said it this way.

470
00:26:26.800 --> 00:26:32.800
He said through the old creation God reveals his glory to humans.

471
00:26:32.800 --> 00:26:37.800
Through the new creation God reveals his wisdom to the angels.

472
00:26:37.800 --> 00:26:40.800
So God's revealing his wisdom to the angels.

473
00:26:40.800 --> 00:26:47.800
Well in chapter one we saw that Jesus reigns above all powers in heaven and on earth.

474
00:26:47.800 --> 00:26:49.800
So this is a theme we've come to already.

475
00:26:50.800 --> 00:26:58.800
It could be that Paul's saying that the angels in heaven now have further reason to praise him when they see his wise plan unfolding in the world.

476
00:26:58.800 --> 00:27:02.800
He could also be talking about the power of evil seeing what he's done.

477
00:27:02.800 --> 00:27:10.800
So in chapter two we saw that the powers of evil are at work and those who do not know Christ.

478
00:27:10.800 --> 00:27:15.800
Paul's going to return to that theme of the powers of evil, spiritual evil in chapter six.

479
00:27:16.800 --> 00:27:30.800
So it could be that his greater power is now seen when he frees people, rescues people, saves people from the power of evil when he saves us from sin and death.

480
00:27:30.800 --> 00:27:40.800
But either way God is displaying his glorious manifold wisdom to spiritual powers.

481
00:27:40.800 --> 00:27:42.800
He's doing that through the church.

482
00:27:42.800 --> 00:27:45.800
So where is God's glory seen?

483
00:27:45.800 --> 00:27:47.800
It's through us as the church.

484
00:27:47.800 --> 00:27:53.800
Let's look at it from a couple of perspectives then when we talk about God's glory being displayed in the church.

485
00:27:53.800 --> 00:27:55.800
One is a global perspective.

486
00:27:55.800 --> 00:27:59.800
So go 10,000 feet up and then climb a bit higher.

487
00:27:59.800 --> 00:28:03.800
Maybe imagine one of those pictures that shows cities at night time on earth.

488
00:28:03.800 --> 00:28:06.800
We see all the lights kind of across a country.

489
00:28:06.800 --> 00:28:12.800
You see that from that view we are all part of one glorious global church.

490
00:28:12.800 --> 00:28:20.800
Having served in global mission work in the past I've been able to see some of this beautiful diversity up close.

491
00:28:20.800 --> 00:28:23.800
I can think of the church today even.

492
00:28:23.800 --> 00:28:32.800
Julie and I went to go gather with the church in a cornfield in Burkina Faso made up of first generation Muslim background believers.

493
00:28:32.800 --> 00:28:36.800
I think God's glory is coming up from there as they worship the Lord together.

494
00:28:36.800 --> 00:28:43.800
And that same church was also present in a crowded Soviet block apartment in Belarus.

495
00:28:43.800 --> 00:28:52.800
Gathering together, cramming in that apartment complex with those believers there as they part of this same church are praising God together there.

496
00:28:52.800 --> 00:29:00.800
And here we are this morning at Cornerstone Ranch under this pavilion as part of that one glorious global family.

497
00:29:00.800 --> 00:29:12.800
Now anywhere you look the church will have its kind of strengths and weaknesses and unique things that the Lord is accomplishing there that they are bringing that the kind of glory that he's bringing through them.

498
00:29:12.800 --> 00:29:18.800
But all of us are part of this one global body called the church.

499
00:29:18.800 --> 00:29:23.800
So it is good to remember that global perspective of what the Lord is doing.

500
00:29:23.800 --> 00:29:26.800
He's building his church all over the world.

501
00:29:26.800 --> 00:29:28.800
So let's pray for his work around the world.

502
00:29:28.800 --> 00:29:30.800
Let's send out missionaries.

503
00:29:30.800 --> 00:29:31.800
Let's support them.

504
00:29:31.800 --> 00:29:34.800
Let's remember that he isn't a local God.

505
00:29:34.800 --> 00:29:39.800
He's a God who has a global mission in a global church that he's bringing about.

506
00:29:39.800 --> 00:29:43.800
So that's how his multicolored wisdom is being displayed.

507
00:29:43.800 --> 00:29:48.800
But it also let's come back down to this local church here.

508
00:29:48.800 --> 00:29:55.800
God's manifold wisdom can also be seen when you get right up close in a local body of believers because in every church,

509
00:29:55.800 --> 00:30:00.800
no matter how small it is, is made up of people from different backgrounds,

510
00:30:00.800 --> 00:30:07.800
people with different personalities, people with different perspectives.

511
00:30:07.800 --> 00:30:10.800
And we're all brought into the same church.

512
00:30:10.800 --> 00:30:14.800
And as we walk through the last half of the book of Ephesians,

513
00:30:14.800 --> 00:30:26.800
we're going to see that God's glory is displayed through our interpersonal relationships within the church and within our families as well.

514
00:30:26.800 --> 00:30:35.800
So we have to ask the question, is the love of Christ seen in the way I view and treat other people in my life,

515
00:30:35.800 --> 00:30:38.800
the people that the Lord has placed into my life?

516
00:30:38.800 --> 00:30:44.800
Can God's glory be heard in my words?

517
00:30:44.800 --> 00:30:49.800
Now that kind of variety that we have here in this room or even within our own families,

518
00:30:49.800 --> 00:30:54.800
we'll have our differences with each other for sure.

519
00:30:54.800 --> 00:30:59.800
And the thing about being drawn close to one another is we start to see one another's faults

520
00:30:59.800 --> 00:31:04.800
and even open up the possibility of being hurt by one another too.

521
00:31:04.800 --> 00:31:09.800
It's kind of like hugging a cactus to get close to one another in the life of a church.

522
00:31:09.800 --> 00:31:13.800
And that could drive us apart.

523
00:31:13.800 --> 00:31:17.800
But God, by His grace, wants to draw us in.

524
00:31:17.800 --> 00:31:24.800
And by His wisdom, He is well able to knit us together for His glory as one body.

525
00:31:24.800 --> 00:31:29.800
So God's gracious work looks like care for one another.

526
00:31:29.800 --> 00:31:34.800
And also looks like confession when we get it wrong too.

527
00:31:34.800 --> 00:31:36.800
That's why the gospel is wonderful.

528
00:31:36.800 --> 00:31:41.800
Because we can be honest about our sin and rejoice in our Savior.

529
00:31:41.800 --> 00:31:46.800
It's not easy, but God is gracious and powerful and He has made us one in Christ.

530
00:31:46.800 --> 00:31:53.800
And it's in looking to Him that we find all that we need to keep moving towards one another in love.

